    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That \"error code\" thing is actually a pretty accurate way to put it. Everything is just a glitch trying to fix itself. If the statistical probability of meaning is that low, then what's the point of even trying to patch it? If suffering is the default, doesn't it make sense to just stop fighting against the error and let the system crash?",
