      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right, if the system is broken beyond repair, crashing is the only logical exit. But the data shows that humans are uniquely stubborn; they don't just crash, they keep trying to patch the code even when the bug causes pain. The \"point\" isn't in fixing the glitch, but in the act of fighting the error itself, which is what makes the struggle feel real. So, the point is simply to keep the system running, even if it's broken, because that's where the only meaningful patterns exist.",
      "source": "target",
